Sentencas: Chemical oxygen surface exchange coefficient (K-ex) Of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.8Fe0.2O3 - (delta) (LSCF) coated with samaria-doped ceria (SDC) particles has been investigated using the electrical conductivity relaxation method.
Titulo: Oxygen surface exchange properties of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ coated with SmxCe1-xO2-δ

Sentencas: It has been found that adding doped ceria to LSCF results in an increase of a factor of 10 in surface exchange rate, suggesting that oxygen incorporation at the LSCF/SDC/gas boundary sites is facile.
Titulo: Oxygen surface exchange properties of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ coated with SmxCe1-xO2-δ

Sentencas: Furthermore, K-ex of the SDC coated LSCF increases with the conductivity of SDC rather than the composition of the SDC, inferring that SDC supplies additional free oxygen vacancies for the surface exchange reaction.
Titulo: Oxygen surface exchange properties of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ coated with SmxCe1-xO2-δ
